│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation arises from simplifying a compare to true based on constraints inferred through     │
│ decomposition, but the decomposition logic does not handle NSW muls; only NUW muls are supported. To be         │
│ conservative and avoid incorrect reasoning, I will modify getConstraintForSolving to bail out when either       │
│ operand is an NSW mul, returning an empty constraint so the pass won’t simplify such compares.                  │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ sed -i '795a \  // Conservatively bail out if operands involve NSW multiplication, which is not handled by      │
│ decomposition logic.\n  // This avoids incorrect constraint reasoning on signed-wrapping muls.\n  {\n    Value  │
│ *A0, *A1, *B0, *B1;\n    if (match(Op0, m_NSWMul(m_Value(A0), m_Value(A1))) ||\n        match(Op1,              │
│ m_NSWMul(m_Value(B0), m_Value(B1))))\n      return {};\n  }'                                                    │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp && submit-patch                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                             │
